<L>__{interior seaside cottage night}
<A>__{mrs. lovett and todd snuggle into bed:}
<C>__{mrs. lovett }
<D>__{think how snug it'll be underneath our flannel when it's just you and me and the english channel...}
<L>__{interior seaside cottage evening}
<A>__{mrs. lovett and todd entertain some unnaturally jolly chums.}
<C>__{mrs. lovett }
<D>__{in our cozy retreat, kept all neat and tidy, we'll have chums over every friday...}
<L>__{exterior beach day}
<A>__{back on the beach.}
<C>__{mrs. lovett }
<D>__{by the sea...}
<C>__{todd }
<D>__{anything you say...}
<A>__{toby pulls mrs. lovett over to examine his little sandcastle as:}
<C>__{mrs. lovett }
<D>__{don't you love the weather by the sea? we'll grow old together by the seaside,}
<P>__{(beckons to todd to join them)}
<D>__{hoo! hoo! by the beautiful sea!}
<A>__{music continues as todd joins them. he kneels with toby to help him work on the sandcastle. mrs. lovett stands, watching them, the picture of the doting mother.}
<C>__{mrs. lovett }
<D>__{it'll be so quiet that who'll come by it except a seagull? hoo! hoo! we shouldn't try it, though, till it's legal, for two hoo!}
